```suggestion
    cocompact   l := by
```
You should never use `` in mathlib (and you should never use `ge` in the statements either). Can you reformulate everything with the inequality swapped?

```suggestion
instance [R1Space ] : IsMeasurablyGenerated (cocompact ) where
  exists_measurable_subset := by
    intro s hs
    obtain t, ht, hts := mem_cocompact.mp hs
    exact (closure t), ht.closure.compl_mem_cocompact, isClosed_closure.measurableSet.compl,
      (compl_subset_compl.2 subset_closure).trans hts 
```
This is more general.

Could you instead deprecate the theorems, with something like
```
@[deprecated] alias Real.atBot_le_cocompact := atBot_le_cocompact -- deprecated on 2024-02-07
@[deprecated] alias Real.atTop_le_cocompact := atTop_le_cocompact -- deprecated on 2024-02-07
```

```suggestion
theorem cocompact_le_atBot_atTop [LinearOrder ] [CompactIccSpace ] :
```
If I'm not mistaken, you're already in the root namespace, so no need to prefix it. Same thing below.

No need to do twice the same proof. If you register an instance
```
instance [CompactIccSpace ] : CompactIccSpace () := sorry
```
(close to the definition of the `CompactIccSpace` class), then you can prove this theorem as
`:= cocompact_le_atBot ( := )`.

```suggestion
    atTop  cocompact  :=
  atBot_le_cocompact ( := )
```
This means that your auxiliary lemma `le_cocompact_aux` is now only used once, and can therefore be inlined in the proof where you need it.

Could you put a simp attribute on this one, and use it throughout the library instead of `Real.cocompact_eq` and `Int.cocompact_eq` (and deprecate these two statements)? Same thing for the next two lemmas and `Nat.cocompact_eq`.
